tool.name: REM

param.name: GGLREMname
param.dialogReference: Input a unique name for each GGLREM run.

param.name: InputCrossSections
param.dialogReference: Select Cross Section polylines created in Step #2.

param.name: GglList
param.displayname: Select Values/Model to Construct Relative Eleavtion Model
param.expression: Custom | Linear Model | Polynomial 2nd | Polynomial 3rd | Polynomial 4th | Polynomial 5th
param.dialogReference:
Select the GGL model(s) you would like to use to construct the REM(s):

  • Custom Model (Requires a CSV table with a column of modeled elevations)

  • Linear Model

  • Quadratic Model

  • 3rd Order Polynomial Model

  • 4th Order Polynomial Model

  • 5th Order Polynomial Model

Prior to selecting a model it is recommended that you evalute the GGL table created in step 3. Professional judgment and site specific knowledge may help reveal the best fit.

param.name: CustomGglTable
param.displayname: Input Custom GGL Table [ONLY IF RUNNING CUSTOM MODEL]

param.name: CustomGglField
param.displayname: Select Field with GGL Values for Detrending
param.dialogReference: Select column with custom modeled elevation vales.

param.name: InputLidar
param.datatype: Raster Layer or Raster Dataset or Raster Catalog

tool.summary:
This fourth tool produces Relative Elevation Models (REM) detrended to the Geomorphic Grade Line (GGL).

  1. First, we input a unique name for each GGLREM run.

  2. Next, we input the Cross Section Feature Class created in Step 2.

  3. Then, we select the GGL model(s) we would like to use for the REM(s)

  4. If, you've created a custom/modified GGL we can then input the table.

  5. Next, we input the LiDAR DEM.

  6. Finally, we select additional REM(s) by preference.
